                    2013 - Current                  


Egerton Capital (UK) LLP

                    Egerton is an active, research-intensive, benchmark agnostic manager which follows a long/short investment approach to invest in liquid, large-cap equities, diversifying across geographies and sectors. The firm employs a bottom-up strategy to identify undervalued equities with significant upside potential, constructing eclectic and uncorrelated portfolios. They employ little or no leverage and typically avoid companies which cannot grow through their own free cashflow on a sustainable basis. Their in-house fundamental research, which includes company visits, is complemented by external sources.                  




Non-Executive Director

                    2007 - 2010                  


Foreign & Colonial Eurotrust Plc

                    Foreign & Colonial Eurotrust Plc provides finance and investment services. It offers a wide range of products and services to institutions, private investors and financial advisers. The company was founded in 1872 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.                  




Independent Non-Executive Director

                    1997 - 2013                  


The European Investment Trust Plc

                    The European Investment Trust Plc engages in the investment in a diversified portfolio of continental European securities. The company was founded on June 28, 1972 and is headquartered in Exeter, the United Kingdom.                  




Chairman, Board of Directors

                    1994 - Prior                  


Cheuvreux de Virieu







